        </div>
        <div class="faq-grid">
          <div class="faq-col">
            <div class="faq-item fade-up"><button type="button" class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false"><span>How much does a plumber cost in Los Angeles?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M6 2v8M2 6h8"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>We provide flat-rate quotes before work starts, so you know the exact cost upfront. Pricing depends on the job — a drain clean is typically less than a water heater replacement. We do not charge by the hour on standard jobs.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item fade-up"><button type="button" class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false"><span>Do you offer same-day plumbing service?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M6 2v8M2 6h8"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. We have licensed plumbers available for same-day and emergency jobs throughout Los Angeles. Call (818) 584-7389 or use the quote form to check availability in your area.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item fade-up"><button type="button" class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false"><span>Are your plumbers licensed in California?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M6 2v8M2 6h8"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. Every plumber in our network holds a valid California C-36 Plumbing Contractor license (or works under one) and carries liability insurance. We vet credentials before they join our network.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item fade-up"><button type="button" class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false"><span>What should I do if I have a burst pipe?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M6 2v8M2 6h8"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Immediately shut off the main water valve to your home to stop water flow. Then call us at (818) 584-7389. We'll get a plumber to you as fast as possible. While waiting, move valuables away from water and do not touch electrical equipment near standing water.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item fade-up"><button type="button" class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false"><span>Do you pull permits for plumbing work?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M6 2v8M2 6h8"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Permit requirements depend on the scope of work. Small repairs typically don't require permits. Larger work like water heater replacement, repiping, or gas line work may require permits — and we handle that process when it applies.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-col">
            <div class="faq-item fade-up"><button type="button" class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false"><span>How do I know if I have a slab leak?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M6 2v8M2 6h8"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Signs include: unexplained increase in water bill, warm spots on floors, sound of running water when no faucets are on, damp or cracked flooring, or low water pressure. If you notice any of these, call us — a slab leak detected early costs far less to repair.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item fade-up"><button type="button" class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false"><span>Should I repair or replace my water heater?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M6 2v8M2 6h8"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Generally: if your unit is under 8 years old and the issue is a component failure (thermostat, element, valve), repair makes sense. If it's over 10–12 years old or has multiple issues, replacement is usually more cost-effective. Our plumbers give you an honest recommendation.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item fade-up"><button type="button" class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false"><span>What causes recurring drain clogs?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M6 2v8M2 6h8"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>Recurring clogs usually indicate a deeper issue — tree roots in your sewer line, significant grease buildup, or a damaged or misaligned pipe. A camera inspection shows exactly what's happening. Hydro-jetting clears the line completely rather than just punching through the blockage.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item fade-up"><button type="button" class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false"><span>Is it safe to use chemical drain cleaners?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M6 2v8M2 6h8"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>We don't recommend it. Chemical drain cleaners can corrode older pipes, damage rubber seals, and are only effective on certain types of clogs. They also create hazardous conditions for plumbers who come after. Professional snaking or hydro-jetting is safer and more effective.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item fade-up"><button type="button" class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false"><span>What areas do you serve?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M6 2v8M2 6h8"/></svg></span></button><div class="faq-answer"><p>We serve Los Angeles and surrounding areas. Enter your ZIP code in the quote form and we'll confirm plumber availability in your area.</p></div></div>
